ADL - Abstract Domain Language
by Christophe VG <contact@christophe.vg>
Copyright 2009-2011, Christophe VG

---

ADL is a generic language to mostly describe hierarchical stuff, like
software ;-)

To experience ADL, point your browser to the examples directory and take a 
look around.

If you are running a system with `make` support you can build everything from
scratch and run our automated test suite.

In a nutshell:
$ make
*** updating submodules
*** updating submodules
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.js
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.min.js
*** generating ADL parser
*** building build/ADL.shared.js
*** building build/ADL.shared.min.js
*** building build/ADL.standalone.js
*** building build/ADL.standalone.min.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.min.js

$ ls build
ADL.cli.js            ADL.parser.js         ADL.shared.min.js     
ADL.standalone.min.js ADL.cli.min.js        ADL.shared.js         
ADL.standalone.js

$ make test
*** updating submodules
*** updating submodules
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.js
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.min.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.min.js
*** running tests
-----------------------
21 tests run.
0 failed.

$ make dist
*** updating submodules
*** updating submodules
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.js
*** building build/ProtoJS.cli.min.js
*** building build/ADL.shared.js
*** building build/ADL.shared.min.js
*** building build/ADL.standalone.js
*** building build/ADL.standalone.min.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.js
*** building build/ADL.cli.min.js
*** packaging ADL distribution
*** packaging ADL src distribution

$ ls dist/
ADL-0.4-10-src.zip ADL-0.4-10.zip     js                 src
